2010-05-02  Ozkan Sezer  <sezeroz@gmail.com>

	First shot at using helpers for winsock headers.
	* _bsd_types.h: New.
	* _socket_types.h: New.
	* _timeval.h: New.
	* in6addr.h: New.
	* inaddr.h: New.
	* time.h: Include _timeval.h. Move struct timeval, timerisset,
	timercmp and timerclear to _timeval.h.
	* sys/time.h: Likewise.
	* ipexport.h: Include inaddr.h and in6addr.h. Move struct in6_addr
	and its related macros to in6addr.h. Move struct in_addr and its
	related macros to inaddr.h.
	* winsock2.h: Same changes as in ipexport.h and time.h. Include
	_timeval.h, _bsd_types.h, _socket_types.h, in6addr.h and inaddr.h.
	Moved u_char, u_short, u_long, u_int and u_int64 to _bsd_types.h.
	Moved struct fd_set and SOCKET types and INVALID_SOCKET, SOCKET_ERROR,
	FD_CLR, FD_SET, FD_ZERO and FD_ISSET macros to _socket_types.h.
	* winsock.h: Same changes as in winsock2.h except for ipv6 stuff.
	* ws2tcpip.h: Same changes as in ipexport.h except for ipv4 stuff.
